NAME
       gPhoto - GNU Project Digital Camera Program

SYNOPSIS
       gphoto  [-h]  [-n]  [-s  # filename ] [-t # filename ] [-p
       filename ]
       gphoto [-d #] [-l filename ]

DESCRIPTION
       gPhoto is an universal, free GTK+  application  that  will
       allow downloading, saving, and manipulation of images from
       several different digital still camera models.

       gPhoto has a basic command line interface, which is handy,
       if  you  want  to set up a web camera, and use gphoto in a
       script, e.g. with Perl/PHP.


USAGE
       gphoto

OPTIONS
       -n     display the # of pictures

       -s # filename
              save image # as filename

       -t # filename
              save thumbnail # as filename

       -p filename
              take picture and save as filename

       -d #   delete image # from camera

       -l filename
              save live preview as filename

       -h     display help screen

FILES
       $HOME/.gphoto/gphotorc
              gPhoto configuration file

